The paper deals with graph theory and specifically focuses on independent sets, matchings, and critical independent sets. The concepts of Konig-Egervary graphs and collections are also discussed. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves some computational aspects, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The concepts of Konig-Egervary graphs and collections are related to graph theory and could place the paper in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
